obo:GO_0003674  a  owl:Class .

gomodel:SYNGO_851  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" , "Rationale: The noradrenaline/norepinephrine transporter (NET) is an integral component of the plasma membranes in axons and axon terminals.\n\nIn cultured SCG neurons, NET-immunoreactivity is localized to axons. ICC demonstrated co-localiation of NET with the synaptic vesicle marker synaptophysin, indicating a presynaptic localization (Fig.10). Pre-embedding immuno-EM using an antibody directed to an intracellular epitope revealed immunoreactivity for NET along the cytoplasmic side of the plasma membrane and within the cytoplasm on synaptic vesicles (Fig.11).\n\nIn the study, a rabbit polyclonal NET antisera was raised against the peptide WERVAYGITPENEHHLVAQRDVR (amino acids 585-607, peptide N585). The specificity of the antibody was validated by immunoprecipitation, immunoblot and immunohistochemistry (Fig.1). No KO-control.. Experimental description: Male Harlan Sprague-Dawley rats (100 g) were sacrificed by decapitation....\nLong-Evans rat pups...\nAdult male Harlan Sprague-Dawley rats were anesthetized with Nembutal (50 mg/kg) and perfused intracardially..." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0755-5899" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0938-8534" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-7351-8706" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_851" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

